Reporting orders, requests, and advice

We can use verb + object + infinite + (to + verb) to report orders, request, and advice.
Common verbs to use include tell, warn, encourage, instruct, ask, order, request, advice. 
Just like in reported speech, you might need to change some pronouns.

"Do it", she told me. => She told me to do it.

"Don't go", they asked. => They asked us not to go.

"Can you help me", she asked. => She asked me to help her.

"You need to study", she encouraged him. => She encouraged him to study.

"Be quiet, please" => They requested us to be quiet.

"You must stay late", he ordered. => He ordered me to stay late.

